      <section eId="sec_CHC-1429">
        <num>CHC 1429</num>
        <heading>1429. Â Application for judicial commitment</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1429__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>If the minor patient admitted to a treatment facility pursuant to this Chapter is a proper candidate for judicial commitment pursuant to Chapter 9 of this Title, the director of the treatment facility, or any interested party, may apply for such commitment under provisions of Chapter 9 of this Title.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1429__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Such a minor patient, hospitalized on an emergency certificate, for whom a petition for judicial commitment has been filed in court may continue to be detained for a further period on order of the court.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=72925</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
